p.k: Giannis Antetokounmpo outdueled fellow MVP candidate Joel Embiid, finishing with 45 points and 13 rebounds and leading Milwaukee to a 128-122 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers as the Bucks clinched the top spot in the conference and the top overall seed in the upcoming playoffs. Antetokounmpo reached 25 or more points and 10-plus rebounds in a game for the 42nd time this season.
